nodes.text: Jaffkee House was a Coruscant Security Force precinct house located on Coruscant. After Ramil was sabotaged by the crime lord Cenevax in the forty-eighth annual Dragonfire Air Rally, the wreckage of his T-22 airspeeder was taken to Jaffkee House, where several Trandoshans working for Cenevax took it away. Jedi Master Dooku and his Padawan Qui-Gon Jinn visited the precinct house, and witnessed the T-22 being taken.

Jaffkee House first appeared in Cavan Scott's 2019 audio drama Dooku: Jedi Lost. It was included as a nod to the character of Jaffkee from the 2011 massively multiplayer online role-playing game Star Wars: The Old Republic.
